The '''way of the traveler''' was a tradition amongst the [[Bosph (species)|Bosph]] [[Species/Legends|species]] in which they [[Tattoo/Legends|tattooed]] maps and [[Star map/Legends|star-charts]] on to their skin representing the places to which they had traveled. The tradition began during a period of Bosph history in which they were mainly nomadic and used the maps to traverse the large plains of their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] [[Bosph/Legends|Bosph]], however after the Bosph were discovered by the rest of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] Bosph continued the tradition whilst traveling away from their homeworld. Those Bosph who were [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]], and so considered [[Ela b'Yentarr]] and members of the [[Bosph government]], had to wear such tattoos as part of the way of the traveler, although it was a choice for other Bosph. One Bosph who observed the tradition was the Bosph [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Bora Boru]].

